%N A391114 Array read by antidiagonals upwards: A(n, k) = if(n mod 2 = 0, floor((n+2^k-2) / 2^k), n * (k*2^k+1) + 1).
%C A391114 Does for every column k iterating n -> A(n, k) always reach 1 (one cycle 1 -> k*2^k+2 -> k+1 -> ... -> 1)? For k=1 we have the Collatz or 3x+1 problem (see A006370).
%F A391114 A(2*n+1, k) = A(2*n-1, k) + 2 * A002064(k).
%F A391114 A(n, k) = A(n-2, k) + A(n-2^k, k) - A(n-2-2^k, k).
%F A391114 G.f. of column k: ((k*2^k+2) * x + x^2 + (2*k*2^k+2) * (x^3 - x^(2^k+1)) / (1 - x^2) + k*2^k * x^(2^k+1)) / ((1 - x^2) * (1 - x^(2^k))).
